1
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:33,914
Logan, what are you doing here?

2
00:00:36,281 --> 00:00:37,709
I want you to find my mother.

3
00:00:40,202 --> 00:00:42,619
Relax, I'm not asking you to drag the lake.

4
00:00:44,072 --> 00:00:45,906
My mother didn't really kill herself.

5
00:00:46,448 --> 00:00:47,605
Come inside, okay?

6
00:00:53,337 --> 00:00:54,942
Veronica, she's not dead.

7
00:00:56,905 --> 00:00:59,448
What makes you think she's still alive?

8
00:00:59,571 --> 00:01:01,558
Why does everyone assume that she's not?

9
00:01:02,172 --> 00:01:03,468
I mean, there's no body.

10
00:01:04,878 --> 00:01:08,173
What about the woman who saw her jump? It's been on every channel.

11
00:01:08,260 --> 00:01:11,090
If she's on the tv, she must be telling the truth.

12
00:01:11,510 --> 00:01:13,200
But her credit cards were missing.

13
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:17,130
Doesn't that seem like... I don't know, a clue?

14
00:01:18,117 --> 00:01:20,621
You don't jump off a bridge with your platinum card.

15
00:01:20,734 --> 00:01:22,591
- Logan, I-- 
- I know my mother!

16
00:01:23,529 --> 00:01:24,383
Okay...

17
00:01:26,318 --> 00:01:28,106
I heard she left a note.

18
00:01:28,316 --> 00:01:30,621
Well, yeah, she wants people to think she's dead.

19
00:01:31,797 --> 00:01:35,929
But if she was going to really do the deed, it would be chardonnay and sleeping pills.

20
00:01:36,524 --> 00:01:40,722
You know, she wouldn't risk being found bug-eyed and bloated in some shrimp net.

21
00:01:41,987 --> 00:01:43,538
I'll see what I can find out.

22
00:01:44,941 --> 00:01:45,929
You know what...

23
00:01:48,352 --> 00:01:51,341
I just need to know she's okay.

24
00:01:56,025 --> 00:01:58,505
Scholars! Thinkers!

25
00:01:59,269 --> 00:02:00,706
Learned charges!

26
00:02:02,436 --> 00:02:03,685
You asked for it.

27
00:02:04,099 --> 00:02:04,909
You got it.

28
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:09,133
World history review, roundup and death match.

29
00:02:10,223 --> 00:02:11,662
Who will reign supreme?

30
00:02:12,093 --> 00:02:16,766
Will it be the age of enlightenment rock stars?!

31
00:02:18,174 --> 00:02:23,454
Or will it be the children of the industrial revolution?!

32
00:02:25,769 --> 00:02:28,051
Blood is in the air.

33
00:02:28,585 --> 00:02:31,175
Blood! Round one!

34
00:02:31,661 --> 00:02:33,541
Let's take a look at the board!

35
00:02:35,517 --> 00:02:41,308
The question is: what are five leading causes of the fall of the roman empire?

36
00:02:41,629 --> 00:02:44,297
Team captain Corazon Soliman, your answer?

37
00:02:44,379 --> 00:02:46,658
The huns kicked their ass.

38
00:02:48,021 --> 00:02:51,620
The correct answer was invading germanic hordes.

39
00:02:52,612 --> 00:02:53,652
Judges?

40
00:02:54,723 --> 00:02:58,204
Judges award the point! Children of the industrial revolution,

41
00:02:58,286 --> 00:03:00,430
you control the board!

42
00:03:02,484 --> 00:03:03,795
You know the rules.

43
00:03:04,527 --> 00:03:06,984
I can call on any team member.

44
00:03:07,926 --> 00:03:11,638
Who will be the weakest link?

45
00:03:13,789 --> 00:03:16,836
Wallace Fennel, show me what you got.

46
00:03:17,087 --> 00:03:18,473
All right, Mr. Rooks.

47
00:03:18,822 --> 00:03:21,039
They relied too much on slave labor.

48
00:03:21,223 --> 00:03:23,871
Can I see "slave labor"?!

49
00:03:27,767 --> 00:03:28,991
Two more answers.

50
00:03:30,563 --> 00:03:36,784
Uh-oh. I see someone hiding back there, trying to disappear completely.

51
00:03:37,428 --> 00:03:39,092
Carrie bishop...

52
00:03:39,318 --> 00:03:41,545
sock it to me, baby!

53
00:03:42,807 --> 00:03:45,150
The answer is, I'm not pregnant.

54
00:03:45,218 --> 00:03:49,072
So you can quit dodging my calls, and you can keep your money to "take care of it."

55
00:03:49,236 --> 00:03:52,226
And while we're at it, here's your key back.

56
00:03:52,318 --> 00:03:54,059
I won't be needing it anymore.

57
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:31,538
Are you okay?

58
00:04:32,315 --> 00:04:34,118
Oh, been better.

59
00:04:38,869 --> 00:04:40,457
She's making it up, you know.

60
00:04:41,368 --> 00:04:46,360
I never touched that girl. I've never seen her outside of class.

61
00:04:46,503 --> 00:04:47,353
I know.

62
00:04:47,972 --> 00:04:49,570
Yeah, but it's not going to matter.

63
00:04:50,286 --> 00:04:54,797
Class has been out less than a minute and I would guess that...

64
00:04:55,152 --> 00:04:57,721
everyone in this school has heard by now.

65
00:04:59,415 --> 00:05:01,182
That's probably a good guess.

66
00:05:01,572 --> 00:05:03,517
This is all I ever wanted to do.

67
00:05:06,245 --> 00:05:09,467
- And it's over. 
- Not if I can help it.

68
00:05:18,068 --> 00:05:24,525
Young teacher, the subject of schoolgirl fantasy.

69
00:05:24,669 --> 00:05:30,976
She wants him so badly knows what she wants to be.

70
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:34,437
Temptation, frustration,

71
00:05:34,544 --> 00:05:38,010
so bad it makes him cry.

72
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:41,216
Her bus stop, she's waiting;

73
00:05:41,369 --> 00:05:44,204
his car is warm and dry...

74
00:05:44,341 --> 00:05:45,839
That's rough, man.

75
00:05:46,974 --> 00:05:48,865
Don't look to me for sympathy.

76
00:05:49,434 --> 00:05:54,460
Carrie has had a long and storied reign as the gossip queen of Neptune High.

77
00:05:54,886 --> 00:05:56,080
You get a crown with that?

78
00:05:57,498 --> 00:05:58,870
Do something for me?

79
00:05:59,571 --> 00:06:00,488
Let me guess:

80
00:06:01,025 --> 00:06:02,659
borrow her permanent file?

81
00:06:02,782 --> 00:06:05,623
I remember when you were new and eager to please.

82
00:06:05,910 --> 00:06:06,932
Good times.

83
00:06:08,475 --> 00:06:09,141
Hey!

84
00:06:11,613 --> 00:06:13,424
Can I ask you kind of a weird favor?

85
00:06:13,784 --> 00:06:14,901
Depends how weird.

86
00:06:15,487 --> 00:06:19,401
Our family physician just retired to Death Valley... literally.

87
00:06:19,472 --> 00:06:21,419
I know it sounds like a metaphor, but it's not.

88
00:06:21,756 --> 00:06:24,521
Anyway, we need a new general practitioner.

89
00:06:24,854 --> 00:06:28,740
- Can I get the name of yours? 
- Sure. Dr. Al Levine. He's in the book.

90
00:06:28,822 --> 00:06:30,342
- Thanks. 
- Yeah, no problem.

91
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:32,549
He's kind of expensive, though.

92
00:06:32,641 --> 00:06:33,885
We've got insurance.

93
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,671
Al Levine -- got it.

94
00:06:39,814 --> 00:06:43,236
It's time to find out what this mystery illness is you're suffering from.

95
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:50,281
Carrie's file.

96
00:06:51,079 --> 00:06:55,446
If you are caught with this, I will disavow any knowledge of you or your mission.

97
00:06:55,821 --> 00:06:56,869
You'll be on your own.

98
00:06:56,956 --> 00:06:57,741
Don't worry.

99
00:06:57,971 --> 00:07:00,377
I've got a cyanide capsule in a false tooth.

100
00:07:00,674 --> 00:07:02,685
If  I'm caught, I'll do the honorable thing.

101
00:07:05,601 --> 00:07:07,531
It's been a privilege knowing you, Mars.

102
00:07:14,268 --> 00:07:17,417
Well, well, well, Carrie. I'm not sure this is the--

103
00:07:17,483 --> 00:07:18,429
It's a good read?

104
00:07:21,559 --> 00:07:22,464
Any news?

105
00:07:23,054 --> 00:07:26,181
I put notices on your mom's credit cards and on her ATM card.

106
00:07:26,248 --> 00:07:26,964
Meaning what?

107
00:07:27,043 --> 00:07:29,883
Meaning a friend of my father's who works at your family bank

108
00:07:29,936 --> 00:07:32,592
will text-message me if any of the cards are used.

109
00:07:32,793 --> 00:07:36,064
And you know that eyewitness that's been clogging up the airwaves?

110
00:07:36,155 --> 00:07:38,015
Yeah.  Opportunistic hag.

111
00:07:38,085 --> 00:07:39,263
That's the one.

112
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:42,413
Well, she's giving a statement at the Sheriff's Department tomorrow.

113
00:07:42,638 --> 00:07:44,737
I'll drop by, see if she's up for a chat.

114
00:07:44,834 --> 00:07:45,812
Well, I'll go with you.

115
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:51,117
Actually, despite popular opinion, you really can't *beat* the truth out of someone.

116
00:07:54,707 --> 00:07:55,755
Listen, I'm going.

117
00:07:56,144 --> 00:07:56,902
You're not.

118
00:07:58,419 --> 00:07:59,846
What are you going to stop me with?

119
00:08:00,522 --> 00:08:04,096
Force of will, strength of character, tenacity, karate chop...

120
00:08:04,172 --> 00:08:07,598
I will know if she's lying, okay. You won't.

121
00:08:09,304 --> 00:08:10,967
Fine. I've got a plan.

122
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,478
Yeah, I'm sure you do.

123
00:08:12,955 --> 00:08:14,829
Hey, Carrie, wait up!

124
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:18,334
Why? Did you want the chance to tell me how much you admired me for my brave stand?

125
00:08:18,421 --> 00:08:21,457
I want to give you a chance to recant before I prove you're lying.

126
00:08:21,576 --> 00:08:22,948
Why do you even care?

127
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:26,001
There aren't many great teachers. Mr. Rooks is one of them.

128
00:08:26,062 --> 00:08:29,503
Yeah, if you can get past the part where he seduces his students.

129
00:08:29,580 --> 00:08:33,246
Hey, Carrie, this is me: Veronica. I know you.

130
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:35,051
You're so naive.

131
00:08:35,979 --> 00:08:37,986
Yeah, that's me... naive.

132
00:08:38,326 --> 00:08:41,991
Mr. Rooks called your parents in for a parent-teacher conference last September.

133
00:08:42,302 --> 00:08:45,575
Hardly seems like something an illicit boyfriend would do.

134
00:08:45,749 --> 00:08:46,834
Believe what you want.

135
00:08:46,987 --> 00:08:50,147
Never cared what you thought of me before, no reason to start now.

136
00:08:58,897 --> 00:08:59,716
Hey, sweetie.

137
00:09:00,043 --> 00:09:00,672
Hey.

138
00:09:00,796 --> 00:09:03,899
Hey, you know a teacher named Chuck Rooks? Teaches history?

139
00:09:04,052 --> 00:09:05,409
Yeah, I'm in his class.

140
00:09:05,521 --> 00:09:08,994
Oh, good, good. I want you to find out whatever you can about him.

141
00:09:09,081 --> 00:09:09,772
Why?

142
00:09:09,941 --> 00:09:13,590
Well, the parents of a girl named Carrie Bishop just hired us to investigate.

143
00:09:13,668 --> 00:09:17,160
Apparently, Carrie filed a sexual-harassment claim against him this afternoon.

144
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:18,290
They want him fired.

145
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,340
What's wrong?

146
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,150
Calm down. What are you so upset about?

147
00:09:31,245 --> 00:09:35,730
Mr. Rooks is an amazing teacher; one of the few good teachers at Neptune High.

148
00:09:35,801 --> 00:09:38,383
And you're just going to join the witch-hunt to get him fired?

149
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:42,602
I'm just running a background check. I'm not organizing a stoning in the town square.

150
00:09:42,664 --> 00:09:46,370
For the record, I can't help you. I've already volunteered to work with him.

151
00:09:46,435 --> 00:09:49,367
You know how I dread going to that school every day?

152
00:09:49,441 --> 00:09:52,304
His class is one of the few things that I look forward to.

153
00:09:52,385 --> 00:09:54,423
Well, I'm sorry. This is my business, honey.

154
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:57,679
It's what I do. Besides, the girl deserves to be heard.

155
00:09:57,741 --> 00:09:59,195
No, actually, she doesn't.

156
00:09:59,261 --> 00:10:01,602
She's a liar and a gossip and a manipulator.

157
00:10:01,668 --> 00:10:03,737
- What makes you think that? 
- I just do.

158
00:10:04,807 --> 00:10:07,710
Well, I can't drop a case based on a feeling you have. I'm sorry.

159
00:10:08,928 --> 00:10:09,751
Fine.

160
00:10:10,285 --> 00:10:12,107
You can answer your own phone.

161
00:10:15,701 --> 00:10:18,549
- I'm surprised I lasted as long as I did. 
- I know.

162
00:10:18,662 --> 00:10:22,465
I mean, of all of the girls in the school Duncan could have gone out with... Veronica Mars?

163
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:25,052
I mean, how insane is that?

164
00:10:25,168 --> 00:10:27,508
- He's out of his mind. 
- That's for sure.

165
00:10:27,965 --> 00:10:30,187
She really got her claws into him.

166
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,067
You know, I actually sort of feel sorry for the guy.

167
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:34,386
You know all she's after is his money.

168
00:10:34,462 --> 00:10:37,345
No, I mean, he's literally crazy. Like looney-bin crazy.

169
00:10:37,417 --> 00:10:38,460
What are you talking about?

170
00:10:38,542 --> 00:10:41,416
You know how Brian's brother is a resident at the hospital?

171
00:10:41,554 --> 00:10:45,839
Brian told Ashley that last week, Duncan was brought in kicking and screaming,

172
00:10:45,891 --> 00:10:48,461
foaming at the mouth, calling out Veronica's name.

173
00:10:48,542 --> 00:10:50,954
It took like three orderlies to get him in a straight jacket.

174
00:10:51,149 --> 00:10:52,071
Come on!

175
00:10:52,275 --> 00:10:53,397
That's what I heard.

176
00:11:00,128 --> 00:11:03,749
Carrie Bishop and Susan Knight. Go figure.

177
00:11:12,106 --> 00:11:13,482
We should do this more often.

178
00:11:15,644 --> 00:11:16,785
Thank you, detective.

179
00:11:19,563 --> 00:11:20,573
That's her.

180
00:11:22,672 --> 00:11:25,591
Down, boy. Relax, I've got it covered.

181
00:11:27,088 --> 00:11:28,356
White trash walking.

182
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:32,462
I know, gadgets and all.

183
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:38,566
Ms. Stanton. Cliff McCormack from "Weekly World News."

184
00:11:38,617 --> 00:11:41,090
My boss is very interested in your story.

185
00:11:41,162 --> 00:11:44,265
Are we talking an exclusive, or what? 'Cause I'm getting lots of offers.

186
00:11:44,341 --> 00:11:45,866
Definitely an exclusive.

187
00:11:45,964 --> 00:11:47,091
Well, what's the offer?

188
00:11:47,182 --> 00:11:52,810
It depends on what you've got. Did she look intoxicated, drugged up, bruised?

189
00:11:52,957 --> 00:11:54,683
If you'd like, sure.

190
00:11:54,836 --> 00:11:59,173
So, what?! You couldn't get on "Springer" this week, so you make lies up about my mom?

191
00:11:59,255 --> 00:12:02,748
You know, I am sure the trailer payments must be high.

192
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:06,884
- And what with the high price of spam these days-- 
- Okay, enough.

193
00:12:08,876 --> 00:12:11,211
Thanks, Cliff. You're the best.

194
00:12:11,319 --> 00:12:14,365
If by "best" you mean "willing." You owe me one, kid.

195
00:12:19,117 --> 00:12:19,920
Hey.

196
00:12:21,179 --> 00:12:21,815
Hi.

197
00:12:24,068 --> 00:12:28,266
I have to take care of something. I'll be like two seconds. Stay calm.

198
00:12:28,594 --> 00:12:31,435
Finding out what that woman is about is good news.

199
00:12:36,514 --> 00:12:37,416
Deputy...

200
00:12:38,281 --> 00:12:39,360
What  do you want, Veronica?

201
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,662
A chance to explain.

202
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,842
What's to explain? You used me. I get it.

203
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:45,080
Lilly Kane was my best friend.

204
00:12:45,678 --> 00:12:48,248
Listen, I know all about your dad and the murder investigation--

205
00:12:48,336 --> 00:12:51,387
No, you don't. You know the story that everyone else knows.

206
00:12:51,464 --> 00:12:53,062
A guy confessed. He said he did it.

207
00:12:54,947 --> 00:12:58,592
Did you know that the head of security at Kane Software was the one

208
00:12:58,627 --> 00:13:00,824
that made the tip call that got Abel Koontz arrested?

209
00:13:01,278 --> 00:13:05,299
Did you know that your own crime-scene photos make it impossible for Abel

210
00:13:05,361 --> 00:13:09,324
to have left the Kane house with a pair of Lilly's shoes that they found on his houseboat?

211
00:13:09,406 --> 00:13:13,332
Did you know there's a traffic ticket that proves that Lilly's time of death is three hours off?

212
00:13:13,419 --> 00:13:14,660
How do you know all this?

213
00:13:14,755 --> 00:13:19,307
I know all of this because I have done everything I could to get to the truth...

214
00:13:19,727 --> 00:13:23,619
including using you. And I'm really sorry about that.

215
00:13:23,685 --> 00:13:27,022
But I used you, then fell for you, not the other way around.

216
00:13:28,038 --> 00:13:29,113
You fell for me?

217
00:13:42,647 --> 00:13:43,536
Hello?

218
00:13:50,274 --> 00:13:51,948
Hey, Veronica...

219
00:13:53,494 --> 00:13:56,741
Uh, come on in. Meet my daughter, Olivia.

220
00:14:04,238 --> 00:14:05,470
Hi, Olivia.

221
00:14:06,577 --> 00:14:08,874
I'm one of your dad's students, Veronica.

222
00:14:09,469 --> 00:14:11,358
She must be going through a shy phase.

223
00:14:11,464 --> 00:14:13,811
No, not really. She's usually pretty gregarious.

224
00:14:13,913 --> 00:14:15,925
She must really dislike you.

225
00:14:16,488 --> 00:14:17,799
There's a club she can join.

226
00:14:17,988 --> 00:14:22,915
Sweetie, why don't you go finish your coloring. I'll come in and join you, okay?

227
00:14:27,832 --> 00:14:28,700
There you go.

228
00:14:32,064 --> 00:14:33,108
She's adorable.

229
00:14:33,257 --> 00:14:36,774
Well, if you get past her megalomania and reactionary politics...

230
00:14:37,634 --> 00:14:41,008
I get her on the weekends. My ex-wife has her during the week.

231
00:14:41,495 --> 00:14:43,303
I'm sorry to intrude on your weekend.

232
00:14:43,409 --> 00:14:45,134
Oh, no problem. What's on your mind?

233
00:14:45,785 --> 00:14:50,065
A few months ago, you called a parent-teacher conference with Carrie's parents?

234
00:14:50,266 --> 00:14:52,774
- How would you know that? 
- I can't reveal my sources.

235
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:58,324
Uh... Veronica, I appreciate your offer of help. It's very generous.

236
00:14:58,396 --> 00:15:00,690
But I really think this is an adult matter.

237
00:15:00,782 --> 00:15:04,837
Right now, Carrie's parents have a private investigator running a background check on you.

238
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,177
There's going to be a hearing.

239
00:15:06,261 --> 00:15:09,921
If the school board believes Carrie's allegations, you'll never teach again.

240
00:15:10,003 --> 00:15:13,976
Her parents came to see me about her grades. I gave her a "C" on her midterm paper.

241
00:15:14,412 --> 00:15:19,183
She thought it was unfair that the black mark on her transcript would keep her out of Cornell.

242
00:15:19,245 --> 00:15:22,660
Do you suppose that's why she's after you -- spoiling her Ivy League dreams?

243
00:15:22,721 --> 00:15:23,945
Honestly, I couldn't tell you.

244
00:15:24,058 --> 00:15:26,398
Do you have anyone representing you at the school board hearing?

245
00:15:26,556 --> 00:15:28,015
Mmm, faculty union rep.

246
00:15:28,152 --> 00:15:29,029
Who's that?

247
00:15:29,736 --> 00:15:31,082
You're looking at him.

248
00:15:38,335 --> 00:15:39,423
Any messages?

249
00:15:46,157 --> 00:15:49,304
Veronica... I know you admire this guy,

250
00:15:49,382 --> 00:15:52,724
and I encourage you to stand up for your convictions when you think you're right.

251
00:15:53,124 --> 00:15:56,806
But Rooks is a bad egg and I don't want you getting hurt when the whole story comes out.

252
00:15:56,893 --> 00:15:58,392
I'm sorry. I believe him.

253
00:15:58,598 --> 00:16:01,317
Carrie kept a very detailed diary of her affair with him.

254
00:16:01,398 --> 00:16:03,145
It's full of times and dates.

255
00:16:03,323 --> 00:16:07,866
She recorded the very date of a weekend she spent in a hotel with him when her parents were out of town.

256
00:16:08,806 --> 00:16:11,997
She writes about him taking her to a fancy restaurant in San Diego

257
00:16:12,052 --> 00:16:15,806
after she won the District Extemporaneous Speaking Competition.

258
00:16:15,888 --> 00:16:18,259
So? That doesn't prove anything.

259
00:16:18,402 --> 00:16:22,278
I could write down that I met Kid Rock every weekend at the Hedonism Lodge

260
00:16:22,355 --> 00:16:25,473
