268
00:16:54,968 --> 00:16:56,537
End of the day would be best.

269
00:16:56,706 --> 00:16:58,862
I have band practice after school.

270
00:16:58,968 --> 00:17:02,523
- How's 5:00? 
- 5:00 is great. Thanks.

271
00:17:04,519 --> 00:17:09,066
I'm no doctor,but I'm pretty sure Penicillin will clear that problem right up.

272
00:17:09,147 --> 00:17:10,806
Can't say I was expecting you.

273
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:15,623
Yeah. Yeah, I usually avoid buildings with stained glass.

274
00:17:16,152 --> 00:17:18,506
That's why you haven't come to visit.

275
00:17:20,366 --> 00:17:25,265
There's a woman who saw my mom get out of her car and get in a van with a mysterious stranger.

276
00:17:25,358 --> 00:17:30,585
There's also a jungle tribe that worships Donald Trump's hair. It's a tabloid.

277
00:17:30,656 --> 00:17:33,524
So the girl with the pig arm can't really bowl?

278
00:17:34,711 --> 00:17:36,612
I just don't want you to get your hopes up.

279
00:17:36,713 --> 00:17:38,792
I'm not paying you to worry about my hopes.

280
00:17:39,008 --> 00:17:40,892
I'm paying you to follow leads.

281
00:17:41,002 --> 00:17:42,538
I wasn't aware you were paying me.

282
00:17:42,618 --> 00:17:46,666
This isn't a favor, it's a job, you know. I mean, we're not exchanging friendship bracelets.

283
00:17:46,757 --> 00:17:47,870
I'll stop braiding.

284
00:17:47,958 --> 00:17:52,426
The woman said my mom was laughing and having fun.

285
00:17:53,901 --> 00:17:56,421
And so do whatever it is you do and track her down.

286
00:17:56,601 --> 00:17:59,134
Sondra Bolan of Sunset Springs.

287
00:17:59,464 --> 00:18:01,440
How am I going to find her?

288
00:18:05,949 --> 00:18:09,870
In Sunset Springs. Sondra Bolan.

289
00:18:10,582 --> 00:18:11,959
I'll put it on your bill.

290
00:18:13,225 --> 00:18:16,956
Hi, Sondra. This is Veronica of "The National Instigator."

291
00:18:17,049 --> 00:18:20,444
I had a few follow-up questions on your Lynn Echolls story.

292
00:18:21,596 --> 00:18:23,987
Actually, in person is a lot better.

293
00:18:25,139 --> 00:18:28,732
No, Tuesday night's no good -- newspaper work night.

294
00:18:28,815 --> 00:18:29,691
What are you doing?

295
00:18:29,849 --> 00:18:32,072
Any chance you're available right now?

296
00:18:34,561 --> 00:18:38,201
So I'm not sure how much you were paid for the last interview, but--

297
00:18:38,287 --> 00:18:41,917
Oh, I wasn't paid. I thought people should know the truth

298
00:18:42,122 --> 00:18:45,506
with that woman lying on every talk show.

299
00:18:46,131 --> 00:18:48,159
So is there anything else you remember?

300
00:18:48,471 --> 00:18:52,254
The  model of the van? Maybe a piece of the license plate?

301
00:18:52,357 --> 00:18:55,264
Honestly, I was just so excited to see Lynn.

302
00:18:55,378 --> 00:18:57,728
I thought they were filming a movie or something.

303
00:18:59,905 --> 00:19:01,891
Have you ever seen Lynn Echolls before?

304
00:19:02,035 --> 00:19:05,218
Once. The premiere of "Delta Blue Bombers."

305
00:19:05,368 --> 00:19:07,482
She was on the red carpet with Aaron.

306
00:19:07,744 --> 00:19:10,046
I must have seen that movie a hundred times.

307
00:19:10,196 --> 00:19:11,486
A hundred times?

308
00:19:11,584 --> 00:19:12,663
I can check if you want.

309
00:19:18,331 --> 00:19:21,194
So the van... in the interview, you said the van was blue?

310
00:19:21,286 --> 00:19:25,519
It was the van from "The Pursuit of Happiness." The exact van.

311
00:19:25,602 --> 00:19:26,821
You mean the exact model?

312
00:19:26,902 --> 00:19:29,729
No, the actual van from the movie.

313
00:19:30,242 --> 00:19:33,555
Lynn and Aaron met on the set of "The Pursuit of Happiness," you know.

314
00:19:33,911 --> 00:19:35,570
They were so young then.

315
00:19:36,379 --> 00:19:40,434
I don't know why anyone could ever think she'd kill herself.

316
00:19:40,874 --> 00:19:43,203
She is the luckiest woman in the world.

317
00:19:43,318 --> 00:19:44,151
Excuse me.

318
00:19:50,505 --> 00:19:52,215
I would have done the same thing.

319
00:19:52,421 --> 00:19:53,224
Done what?

320
00:19:53,469 --> 00:19:57,581
If it was my mother, I would have let myself believe that story.

321
00:20:01,244 --> 00:20:02,937
Hey, manners, Opie!

322
00:20:03,987 --> 00:20:05,584
What, did he lose a puka shell?

323
00:20:06,044 --> 00:20:06,792
No...

324
00:20:08,385 --> 00:20:12,025
just the last ounce of hope that his mother was still alive.

325
00:20:20,632 --> 00:20:22,915
Is that lasagna I smell?

326
00:20:23,089 --> 00:20:24,805
Keith Mars' secret recipe.

327
00:20:25,445 --> 00:20:27,805
You double the cheese. Your secret is out.

328
00:20:29,398 --> 00:20:30,739
You're making salad?

329
00:20:32,454 --> 00:20:34,405
I know pity cooking when I see it.

330
00:20:35,307 --> 00:20:36,867
There must be more bad news.

331
00:20:38,429 --> 00:20:40,862
Maybe we should wait 'til after dinner, huh?

332
00:20:41,162 --> 00:20:44,461
Spill it. I promise I won't let it ruin my appetite.

333
00:20:45,594 --> 00:20:49,129
Rooks was fired from his last job at a private school.

334
00:20:50,201 --> 00:20:54,604
His file is sealed, but the complaint came from the parents of two girls.

335
00:20:58,490 --> 00:21:01,504
- I want to see Carrie's journal. 
- You know I can't let you.

336
00:21:05,457 --> 00:21:06,902
There better be dessert.

337
00:21:08,615 --> 00:21:13,502
If I'm going to save Mr. Rooks' job, I have to get my hands on this supposed diary.

338
00:21:20,998 --> 00:21:24,080
Unfortunately, dad's changed the combination.

339
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:28,631
It's the rare individual who chooses meaningless numbers as a combination.

340
00:21:28,713 --> 00:21:29,784
He taught me that.

341
00:21:31,878 --> 00:21:35,701
Nine times out of ten, an individual will select numbers that mean something --

342
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:39,302
birthdays, anniversaries, addresses.

343
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:42,691
Of course, dad is smarter than that.

344
00:21:43,582 --> 00:21:47,796
You wouldn't believe the number of people who keep the combination written down on a post-it,

345
00:21:47,954 --> 00:21:53,434
or tacked to a bulletin board, or scribbled on a birthday page of their page-a-day calendar.

346
00:21:53,741 --> 00:21:56,239
Somehow, I doubt dad's that careless.

347
00:21:59,326 --> 00:22:03,525
Then again, he'll be glad to know how much I've soaked up listening to him.

348
00:22:10,753 --> 00:22:12,587
And what do we have here?

349
00:22:29,415 --> 00:22:32,720
I suspect there's also a lesson to be learned here.

350
00:22:39,504 --> 00:22:41,940
Hey, honey. What have you been up to?

351
00:22:43,477 --> 00:22:46,180
Tell me where to put your "Father of the Year" trophy.

352
00:22:46,261 --> 00:22:48,065
'Cause there's some place I'd like to put it.

353
00:22:48,187 --> 00:22:50,793
Wow. Good thing I didn't go with a bear trap.

354
00:22:52,363 --> 00:22:53,870
This is not funny.

355
00:22:54,091 --> 00:22:57,102
I need to see that diary. She's lying. I know it.

356
00:22:57,173 --> 00:22:59,616
I can feel it with every fiber of my being.

357
00:22:59,676 --> 00:23:01,618
Honey, you don't have to get all blue in the face.

358
00:23:01,679 --> 00:23:02,857
You're patronizing me?

359
00:23:02,943 --> 00:23:05,089
To be fair, I am your patron.

360
00:23:05,191 --> 00:23:08,477
The Bishops are going to use your credit card research and that diary

361
00:23:08,539 --> 00:23:10,505
to prove the two of them were together.

362
00:23:10,674 --> 00:23:14,028
Just give me the dates and times -- I don't have to read the diary.

363
00:23:14,094 --> 00:23:16,640
Do you want to be responsible for taking a good man down?

364
00:23:16,726 --> 00:23:18,676
Destroying his reputation?

365
00:23:19,021 --> 00:23:20,767
Can you possibly relate?

366
00:23:22,641 --> 00:23:24,585
Dates and times -- that's it.

367
00:23:35,508 --> 00:23:38,496
If you're looking for my trophy, it's back by auto shop.

368
00:23:38,978 --> 00:23:42,270
Lube job? Or can you medal in stealing hubcaps?

369
00:23:42,382 --> 00:23:45,148
Is this 1970? Rims, baby.

370
00:23:45,231 --> 00:23:46,867
So you got a trophy for a rim job?

371
00:23:47,682 --> 00:23:50,344
Forget it. I got some information for you.

372
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:53,611
Finally, a Deep Throat to call my own.

373
00:23:53,718 --> 00:23:57,502
I'm not going to touch that one. Uh, I hear this freshman kid's been shooting his mouth off

374
00:23:57,569 --> 00:24:01,040
that he's got proof that Lynn Echolls jumped and he's gonna make millions.

375
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:01,931
Who's the kid?

376
00:24:02,125 --> 00:24:03,345
Do you want me to find out?

377
00:24:03,466 --> 00:24:04,793
Do you even have to ask?

378
00:24:07,461 --> 00:24:09,498
- Can I ask you something? 
- Shoot.

379
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:12,611
Why were you fired from your last job?

380
00:24:13,358 --> 00:24:15,653
- How on earth do you know-- 
- I just do.

381
00:24:15,832 --> 00:24:20,387
Wow. Maybe I should give more credence to the teacher's lounge gossip.

382
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:22,261
Colleagues said you were...

383
00:24:24,144 --> 00:24:25,651
unique...

384
00:24:27,106 --> 00:24:28,023
gifted...

385
00:24:31,004 --> 00:24:31,844
unsettling.

386
00:24:31,952 --> 00:24:35,009
I was hoping for delightful, but what can you do.

387
00:24:37,141 --> 00:24:38,032
So...

388
00:24:39,108 --> 00:24:40,869
My firing... yeah.

389
00:24:42,291 --> 00:24:44,995
It was an all-girls school on the conservative side.

390
00:24:45,660 --> 00:24:51,308
I had the temerity to suggest U.S. Imperialism wasn't necessarily a good thing.

391
00:24:51,867 --> 00:24:57,688
They thought I was trying to turn their daughters into little berét-wearing, clove-smoking Bolsheviks.

392
00:24:57,847 --> 00:24:59,465
- Were you? 
- Nyet!

393
00:25:00,364 --> 00:25:01,109
That's it?

394
00:25:01,272 --> 00:25:07,039
Well, that, and I was driving an '89 Harley. Didn't really endear me to the administration.

395
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,796
Thanks, Mr. Rooks.

396
00:25:11,615 --> 00:25:13,791
Do svidaniya, Veronica.

397
00:25:17,428 --> 00:25:21,359
I'm giving you another chance. Drop the complaint against Mr. Rooks.

398
00:25:21,463 --> 00:25:24,092
Yeah. I remember when I was in love with him, too.

399
00:25:24,595 --> 00:25:27,708
Did you ever consider that I just really dislike you?

400
00:25:27,779 --> 00:25:30,805
Wow, does that mean you won't be signing my yearbook?

401
00:25:30,898 --> 00:25:33,900
You're still in Mr. Rooks' class. You must not be too shook up.

402
00:25:34,044 --> 00:25:36,371
I need his class to graduate.

403
00:25:36,523 --> 00:25:38,772
And he'll be the one leaving... soon.

404
00:25:38,943 --> 00:25:42,224
All this because he gave you a "C" on your paper? You'd destroy him?

405
00:25:42,321 --> 00:25:43,130
Destroy him?

406
00:25:43,487 --> 00:25:47,906
From where I stand, he's become more popular than ever. I'm the bitch that everyone hates.

407
00:25:48,074 --> 00:25:50,246
Are you interested in details, Veronica?

408
00:25:50,379 --> 00:25:52,345
Can I help enrich your fantasy life?

409
00:25:52,590 --> 00:25:54,777
He says "baby" a lot when he touches you.

410
00:25:54,946 --> 00:25:56,891
His sheets are black, silk.

411
00:25:56,959 --> 00:26:00,178
His mood music is side two of the Rolling Stones' "Tattoo You."

412
00:26:00,461 --> 00:26:03,727
He'll tear up as he tells you the story of his ex-wife leaving him.

413
00:26:03,988 --> 00:26:05,626
You'll turn to jelly.

414
00:26:05,969 --> 00:26:09,052
Yeah, I have that same "Sweet Valley High" book.

415
00:26:09,241 --> 00:26:12,908
You said you spent the night in a hotel with Mr. Rooks on April 23,

416
00:26:12,964 --> 00:26:14,847
but there's a problem with that story, isn't there?

417
00:26:14,935 --> 00:26:17,459
Why don't you tell me? It's obvious you're dying to.

418
00:26:18,576 --> 00:26:24,892
All right. The problem with that story is that you were at an overnight track meet in Sacramento that weekend.

419
00:26:25,215 --> 00:26:28,119
You were part of the winning 1,600-meter relay.

420
00:26:29,945 --> 00:26:31,755
People say you're fast.

421
00:26:41,154 --> 00:26:44,677
Sorry to keep you waiting. I'm always busy at the end of the day.

422
00:26:44,763 --> 00:26:49,025
Those sniffles -- probably just light allergies, not uncommon.

423
00:26:49,121 --> 00:26:50,546
So I can put my shirt back on?

424
00:26:50,666 --> 00:26:52,363
Uh, sure. Yes, of course.

425
00:26:56,816 --> 00:27:01,384
One problem with doctors, besides their fetish for making you wait half-naked in cold rooms,

426
00:27:01,461 --> 00:27:05,609
is they won't just let you ransack their files, even if you ask real nice.

427
00:27:06,273 --> 00:27:11,752
So someone like me has to resort to methods the insurance companies would probably not support.

428
00:27:13,979 --> 00:27:15,224
- Good night, Nancy. 
- Good night.

429
00:27:52,715 --> 00:27:56,655
Okay, yes, I am petite, and it does come in handy every now and then.

430
00:28:25,311 --> 00:28:30,831
I'm generally pretty cool with coincidence, but when Abel Koontz turns out to share a doctor with the Kanes,

431
00:28:30,887 --> 00:28:34,876
that's too much for me to ignore, even if it means getting caught.

432
00:28:35,598 --> 00:28:36,427
Wha--?

433
00:28:37,133 --> 00:28:41,041
Is the doctor here? 'Cause I've been sitting for like an hour.

434
00:28:42,858 --> 00:28:45,899
This experience has ruined me.

435
00:28:47,763 --> 00:28:49,391
I mean, the stories in the newspaper.

436
00:28:49,581 --> 00:28:55,714
My peers in the faculty lounge stop talking when I enter.

437
00:28:55,863 --> 00:29:00,936
Mr. Rooks, do you have any guess why Miss Bishop would file this grievance?

438
00:29:03,589 --> 00:29:07,860
Carrie is a solid "B" student in my class.

439
00:29:08,504 --> 00:29:10,902
She made it very clear she needed an "A"...

440
00:29:14,684 --> 00:29:17,756
but the work just didn't merit it.

441
00:29:18,888 --> 00:29:20,910
My dad left my mom last year,

442
00:29:21,196 --> 00:29:24,285
and I was pretty lost.

443
00:29:25,815 --> 00:29:29,010
Mr. Rooks started giving me rides home from our mock U.N. Meetings,

444
00:29:29,656 --> 00:29:32,313
and we'd just talk. He said that we had a lot in common,

445
00:29:32,384 --> 00:29:36,578
that we'd both been abandoned by people we thought loved us because of his wife.

446
00:29:38,346 --> 00:29:40,689
At first we just kissed,

447
00:29:41,595 --> 00:29:44,569
but... it went beyond that.

448
00:29:45,476 --> 00:29:48,246
When I told him I thought I might be pregnant, he just blew me off.

449
00:29:48,614 --> 00:29:51,795
When I saw him flirting with other girls, I just decided,

450
00:29:52,603 --> 00:29:54,267
"I guess this is what he does."

451
00:29:55,143 --> 00:29:57,263
And I couldn't let him get away with it again.

452
00:29:57,425 --> 00:29:59,690
These are very serious charges, Carrie.

453
00:30:00,499 --> 00:30:03,868
Is there any proof you can offer beyond your testimony?

454
00:30:07,968 --> 00:30:09,816
He sent me text messages all the time.

455
00:30:10,575 --> 00:30:14,435
April 9th: "Let's meet for tutoring. Clothing optional."

456
00:30:15,567 --> 00:30:19,018
April 14th: "I miss your scent. Call me."

457
00:30:20,390 --> 00:30:24,983
April 29th: "come to school without your underwear. You'll be rewarded."

458
00:30:34,127 --> 00:30:35,878
They're addressed to "S.K."

459
00:30:37,721 --> 00:30:39,544
He used to call me "Sweet Knees."

460
00:30:39,758 --> 00:30:41,806
He always wanted me to wear knee socks.

461
00:30:41,879 --> 00:30:46,666
I'm not sure we have proof that Mr. Rooks actually sent you these messages.

462
00:30:46,748 --> 00:30:48,243
Hit the call-back button there.

463
00:31:02,219 --> 00:31:04,848
Mr. Clemmons, can I borrow your cell for a minute?

464
00:31:05,301 --> 00:31:07,228
My car broke down in the parking lot.

465
00:31:19,568 --> 00:31:25,446
Mr. Clemmons, what can you tell us about your interaction with Mr. Rooks that might be relevant?

466
00:31:26,039 --> 00:31:28,067
Well, he's a very popular teacher.

467
00:31:28,165 --> 00:31:32,244
The student body has voted him "best teacher" three of the four years he's been with us.

468
00:31:32,316 --> 00:31:33,392
Thank you, Mr. Clemmons.

469
00:31:34,867 --> 00:31:37,780
Um, Mrs. Fuller, if I may?

470
00:31:42,245 --> 00:31:48,025
Could I ask you to get out your own cell phone and, uh, check the messages?

471
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:58,259
Now check and see if you have messages.

472
00:31:58,353 --> 00:32:00,288
I have three new messages.

473
00:32:00,441 --> 00:32:01,971
Can you read them out loud?

474
00:32:02,366 --> 00:32:06,323
The first one says, "true pirates share their booty."

475
00:32:07,522 --> 00:32:10,573
The second, "I'll be your little spoon."

476
00:32:12,264 --> 00:32:16,097
And finally, "vice principals make the best lovers."

477
00:32:17,987 --> 00:32:19,753
Mind hitting redial?

478
00:32:28,688 --> 00:32:33,194
I think we have to conclude that either the two of you are having an affair...

479
00:32:35,190 --> 00:32:40,474
or that it's extremely easy to create false text messages on someone's cellphone.

480
00:32:50,387 --> 00:32:56,434
In a situation like we have here today, the burden of proof is on the accuser.

481
00:32:56,787 --> 00:33:03,044
We find no conclusive evidence to substantiate the claim that these alleged encounters ever happened.

482
00:33:04,385 --> 00:33:08,558
Mr. Rooks will continue on as a teacher at this school.

483
00:33:17,768 --> 00:33:19,734
You didn't have to come all the way over here.

484
00:33:19,817 --> 00:33:22,822
I know, but I felt really stupid getting out of there with your phone.

485
00:33:23,636 --> 00:33:24,224
Sorry.

486
00:33:24,318 --> 00:33:27,446
Well, I appreciate you hooking me up with password protection.

487
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,109
That's what I do.

