00:33:29,203 --> 00:33:32,203
Hey, you want some pizza? It just got delivered.

489
00:33:32,273 --> 00:33:35,106
They had a two-for-one deal. I'm swimming in it.

490
00:33:35,208 --> 00:33:39,995
Um... one slice. I have this newspaper work night thing.

491
00:33:43,906 --> 00:33:46,862
Nice. You must have a gay friend.

492
00:33:47,106 --> 00:33:51,987
No, I literally duplicated a page from the "Z Gallery" catalog.

493
00:33:52,098 --> 00:33:52,981
Something to drink?

494
00:33:53,210 --> 00:33:54,577
Whatever you're having.

495
00:33:54,965 --> 00:33:56,348
Diet anything is good.

496
00:33:56,626 --> 00:33:58,791
- Can I use your bathroom? 
- Sure, down the hall.

497
00:34:14,406 --> 00:34:15,875
Is that Mick Jagger?

498
00:34:21,011 --> 00:34:25,962
I have to get back to the journalism room. Rain check on the pizza?

499
00:34:26,049 --> 00:34:26,966
Absolutely.

500
00:34:27,483 --> 00:34:28,281
See you tomorrow.

501
00:34:29,554 --> 00:34:35,188
Best way to stop wondering if your favorite teacher was trying to lure you between his black silk sheets?

502
00:34:35,254 --> 00:34:38,230
Research the mystery condition that's causing your ex-boyfriend

503
00:34:38,318 --> 00:34:41,564
and possible half brother to take Oxcarbazepine.

504
00:34:42,086 --> 00:34:46,177
Hmm... it's a drug used to treat type 4 epilepsy.

505
00:34:46,279 --> 00:34:50,651
Symptoms include hysterical, violent, emotional fits that can't be controlled

506
00:34:50,718 --> 00:34:54,528
and are often are accompanied by complete blackouts and loss of memory.

507
00:34:54,651 --> 00:34:55,464
Whatcha doing?

508
00:34:56,693 --> 00:34:58,316
Google-ing myself.

509
00:34:59,602 --> 00:35:01,065
Like I'm the first.

510
00:35:01,982 --> 00:35:03,973
Find out anything interesting?

511
00:35:04,374 --> 00:35:08,084
There's a Veronica Mars in Vermont who sells pinecone porcupines.

512
00:35:15,396 --> 00:35:17,455
Do you know where we keep last year's newspapers?

513
00:35:17,553 --> 00:35:19,733
In the supply cabinet. Why?

514
00:35:19,867 --> 00:35:24,044
I want to see who won last year's District Extemporaneous Speaking Competition.

515
00:35:25,575 --> 00:35:26,769
Okay...

516
00:35:28,296 --> 00:35:29,329
Why?

517
00:35:29,712 --> 00:35:32,135
I want to know if the winner had sweet knees.

518
00:35:35,477 --> 00:35:36,452
I give up.

519
00:35:46,309 --> 00:35:47,888
- What city? 
- Neptune.

520
00:35:48,063 --> 00:35:50,321
I need a listing for the Knight family.

521
00:35:50,521 --> 00:35:52,296
- Ninth street? 
- Is there more than one?

522
00:35:52,389 --> 00:35:53,433
No.

523
00:35:53,854 --> 00:35:55,195
Then that would be it.

524
00:35:55,286 --> 00:35:56,552
Please hold for your number.

525
00:36:10,005 --> 00:36:11,138
Veronica Mars?

526
00:36:11,525 --> 00:36:15,546
Carrie's story is true, isn't it? It just didn't happen to her.

527
00:36:16,418 --> 00:36:20,735
She copied your diary, and it was your cellphone she showed in court.

528
00:36:21,406 --> 00:36:25,604
You got together with Rooks the night you won the Extemporaneous Speaking Competition?

529
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:27,949
S.K. was you, Susan Knight.

530
00:36:30,836 --> 00:36:32,274
My parents disowned me.

531
00:36:34,011 --> 00:36:35,860
I wouldn't tell them who the father is

532
00:36:36,632 --> 00:36:41,768
because I knew if I did, they would press charges for statutory rape, and I don't want that.

533
00:36:41,843 --> 00:36:45,008
There's something I'm not getting. Why would Carrie tell your story?

534
00:36:45,081 --> 00:36:47,042
Because she thought what he did was wrong.

535
00:36:47,799 --> 00:36:49,550
Do you know when I told Mr. Rooks I was pregnant,

536
00:36:49,611 --> 00:36:52,734
he gave me $500 and told me I should go take care of it?

537
00:36:52,807 --> 00:36:55,295
It made her crazy there were no consequences for what he did.

538
00:36:55,367 --> 00:36:57,732
Meanwhile, I had to run out of town in shame?

539
00:36:58,382 --> 00:37:00,225
Look, it made me crazy too, but...

540
00:37:02,207 --> 00:37:03,716
I can't come forward.

541
00:37:05,915 --> 00:37:07,583
I'm just not that brave.

542
00:37:07,686 --> 00:37:13,389
You have no idea. People have put her through hell, and she just took it.

543
00:37:13,527 --> 00:37:15,443
She said most people were supportive of her.

544
00:37:15,467 --> 00:37:16,596
They weren't.

545
00:37:17,732 --> 00:37:19,712
We weren't.

546
00:37:22,288 --> 00:37:24,443
Carrie just went to the mat for you.

547
00:37:24,992 --> 00:37:27,730
One phone call, and you can make it all worth it.

548
00:37:29,184 --> 00:37:33,377
I just happen to have the school board president's cellphone number.

549
00:37:44,314 --> 00:37:45,880
I went to see Susan.

550
00:37:47,637 --> 00:37:48,722
I'm sorry.

551
00:37:49,475 --> 00:37:51,170
A lot of good that does me now.

552
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:55,050
Yo, V. You might want to talk to this freshman.

553
00:37:55,153 --> 00:37:58,123
He's the one who's been shooting his mouth off about Logan's mom.

554
00:37:58,486 --> 00:38:01,133
Hope you don't mind telling that story one more time.

555
00:38:01,722 --> 00:38:04,538
Hey... you paged?

556
00:38:06,141 --> 00:38:09,157
It seems Hart here has something to show us.

557
00:38:11,190 --> 00:38:12,229
Spill.

558
00:38:13,361 --> 00:38:15,219
Me and my friends were filming out by the bay.

559
00:38:15,295 --> 00:38:17,201
We were making this war movie, "Storm on the Beach."

560
00:38:17,283 --> 00:38:18,906
It's just on high def, but it's pretty cool.

561
00:38:19,027 --> 00:38:21,276
- It's these two brothers who get sent to war and-- 
- Don't care.

562
00:38:21,363 --> 00:38:22,207
Point?

563
00:38:23,384 --> 00:38:26,375
We were editing it together, and we noticed something.

564
00:38:33,333 --> 00:38:34,433
Over there! Over there!

565
00:38:34,531 --> 00:38:35,300
I see him!

566
00:38:39,798 --> 00:38:42,622
- Did you see it? 
- Yeah, it sucks, and...?

567
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:45,570
Rewind it. Play it frame by frame.

568
00:38:49,246 --> 00:38:51,151
There! Check out the right side of the bridge.

569
00:38:53,363 --> 00:38:54,690
Holy...

570
00:38:56,865 --> 00:39:00,911
The video's time-stamped 4:37 P.M. Exactly the time when...

571
00:39:01,754 --> 00:39:03,731
she supposedly jumped.

572
00:39:06,009 --> 00:39:09,086
This footage better never make it out into public consumption.

573
00:39:09,153 --> 00:39:10,853
Don't worry about my boy, Hart.

574
00:39:10,982 --> 00:39:14,309
He knows if that happens his last movie will be a snuff film.

575
00:39:14,478 --> 00:39:16,418
And he'll star in it, right?

576
00:39:17,902 --> 00:39:18,794
Come on.

577
00:39:25,066 --> 00:39:26,054
I'm sorry.

578
00:39:28,124 --> 00:39:29,182
So am I.

579
00:39:45,782 --> 00:39:46,678
Logan!

580
00:39:47,482 --> 00:39:48,229
Logan.

581
00:39:49,970 --> 00:39:54,722
Logan, your mom's missing credit card was just used.

582
00:40:00,942 --> 00:40:01,879
Quiet down.

583
00:40:03,068 --> 00:40:05,402
Quiet down, please. I have an announcement to make.

584
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:10,562
I regret to inform you that Mr. Rooks tendered his resignation this morning.

585
00:40:11,335 --> 00:40:13,926
I will be taking over the teaching duties in this class

586
00:40:13,989 --> 00:40:17,926
until a replacement can be found by the administrat--

587
00:40:56,234 --> 00:40:57,882
Mr. Rooks resigned today.

588
00:40:58,081 --> 00:41:02,429
Honey, if I were in trouble, I'd want you on my side.

589
00:41:02,598 --> 00:41:03,934
Well, that's where I'd be.

590
00:41:04,886 --> 00:41:07,457
I'll be home for dinner. Your messages are on your desk.

591
00:41:22,382 --> 00:41:30,400
So... what would you like to know now, Veronica Mars, intrepid girl reporter?

592
00:41:30,748 --> 00:41:31,682
Nothing.

593
00:41:31,859 --> 00:41:34,250
This time I just want you to know what I know.

594
00:41:37,419 --> 00:41:38,893
You're dying, Abel.

595
00:41:39,651 --> 00:41:42,164
You knew you were dying when you confessed.

596
00:41:42,519 --> 00:41:44,260
You didn't kill Lilly Kane.

597
00:41:45,608 --> 00:41:47,792
You're just somebody's patsy.

598
00:41:50,855 --> 00:41:51,709
Guard?

599
00:41:57,244 --> 00:42:00,331
Synchro: Amariss
